The following table lists most [[river]]s of [[Sri Lanka]]. Since Sri Lanka is a trilingual country, some rivers may have a [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]] name (i.e. [[Kalu Ganga]]), while other have an [[English language|English]] name (i.e. [[Kelani River]]). In the Sinhala language, Ganga (ගඟ) translates to "river", where as Oya (ඔය) translates to "smaller river".{{citation needed|date=July 2016}} At {{Convert|335|km|mi|0|abbr=on}}, the [[Mahaweli River]] is the longest river in the island, and has [[drainage basin]] covering more than one-fifth of the island.

